<%- include("partials/header") %>

  <body
    class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900 via-black to-blue-950 min-h-screen flex flex-col"
  >
    <!-- NAVBAR -->

    <nav class="bg-black/40 backdrop-blur-md border-b border-white/10">
      <div
        class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6 py-4 flex justify-between items-center text-white"
      >
        <a href="/" class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold">
          <span
            class="bg-gradient-to-r from-yellow-400 to-orange-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent"
            >Six</span
          ><span class="text-white">Storm</span>
        </a>

        <div class="space-x-4 font-semibold text-sm md:text-base">
          <a href="/" class="hover:text-yellow-400 transition">Home</a>
          <a href="/legal" class="hover:text-yellow-400 transition"
            >Disclaimer</a
          >
          <a href="/privacy-policy" class="hover:text-yellow-400 transition"
            >Privacy Policy</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->

    <div
      class="flex-grow flex items-center justify-center px-4 md:px-6 py-8 md:py-12"
    >
      <div class="max-w-4xl w-full space-y-6">
        <h1
          class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-center text-white mb-8"
        >
          ❓ SixStorm Help Center
        </h1>

        <!-- FAQ 1 -->

        <div
          class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-lg p-5 md:p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-white/20 text-white"
        >
          <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-400">
            1. Is streaming safe and free?
          </h3>

          <p class="mt-3 text-sm md:text-base text-gray-300">
            Our platform acts as an aggregator that provides access to publicly
            available streams and information. We do not host any content
            directly on our servers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 2 -->

        <div
          class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-lg p-5 md:p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-white/20 text-white"
        >
          <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-400">
            2. When does live streaming start?
          </h3>

          <p class="mt-3 text-sm md:text-base text-gray-300">
            Live streaming becomes available when the match begins. Refresh the
            page if the stream does not appear immediately.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 3 -->

        <div
          class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-lg p-5 md:p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-white/20 text-white"
        >
          <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-400">
            3. How can I watch live matches?
          </h3>

          <p class="mt-3 text-sm md:text-base text-gray-300">
            Simply visit the homepage and access the available stream once the
            match goes live.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 4 -->

        <div
          class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-lg p-5 md:p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-white/20 text-white"
        >
          <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-400">
            4. What tournaments are available?
          </h3>

          <p class="mt-3 text-sm md:text-base text-gray-300">
            Major cricket tournaments such as international events and league
            matches may be accessible through third-party sources.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 5 -->

        <div
          class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-lg p-5 md:p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-white/20 text-white"
        >
          <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-400">
            5. Who developed this platform?
          </h3>

          <p class="mt-3 text-sm md:text-base text-gray-300">
            This platform is designed and maintained by
            <span class="text-yellow-400 font-semibold">Naveen Rathore</span>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FOOTER -->

    <%- include("partials/footer") %>
  </body>
</html>
